    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "interesting. so you're saying it was basically a mistake? i was reading some articles that argued it was actually a win because it stopped a massive massacre in Benghazi and upheld the \"responsibility to protect\" doctrine. wouldn't you say that's a valid way to measure success too?",
